Every year, hundreds of thousands of students – including a record 274,000 degree-credit students – choose
The City University of New York
for a multitude of reasons that can be summed up as one: opportunity. Providing a quality, accessible education, regardless of background or means, has been CUNY’s mission since 1847.

Our fall issue is full of good news, starting with the newly ratified agreement between the University and the Professional Staff Congress, the union representing nearly 30,000 full- and part-time faculty and professional staff. Meet the first-ever “CUNY Hero” and a pioneering City College physicist who won one of her field’s top honors; read about CUNY’s groundbreaking SEEK initiative; check out the City Tech trio who made a big splash in the Gulf of Mexico, and much more.
